'''Ontologism''' is a philosophical system most associated with [[Nicholas Malebranche]] (1638–1715) which maintains that God and divine ideas are the first object of our intelligence and the intuition of God the first act of our intellectual knowledge.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/11257a.htm|title=Ontologism|work=[[Catholic Encyclopedia]]}}</ref>
